article.description: — Alex Morales had 19 points and eight rebounds as Wagner extended its win streak to seven games, easily beating Fairleigh Dickinson 95-64 on Monday night.
article.headline: Morales carries Wagner over Fairleigh Dickinson 95-64
article.linkText: Morales carries Wagner over Fairleigh Dickinson 95-64
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Alex Morales had 19 points and eight rebounds as Wagner extended its win streak to seven games, easily beating Fairleigh Dickinson 95-64 on Monday night. Raekwon Rogers had 14 points for Wagner (10-2, 4-0 Northeast Conference). Will Martinez added 14 points. Antoine Jacks had 11 points for the Knights (1-12, 1-2). John Square Jr. added 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
